  'uk-visa-for-us-citizens',
  'UK Visa for US Citizens: The Complete 2026 Guide',
  'Planning to visit, work, or move to the UK as an American in 2026? Here''s everything US citizens need to know about the UK ETA, visitor rules, work visas, and long-stay options — fully updated.',
  'uk visa for us citizens',
  'Matthew Lin',
  11,
  '2026-03-04T00:00:00Z',
  'Planning to visit, work, or move to the UK as an American in 2026? Here''s everything US citizens need to know about the UK ETA, visitor rules, work visas, and long-stay options — fully updated.',
  '[{"type":"paragraph","text":"The United Kingdom has always been one of the most natural international destinations for Americans — shared language, cultural familiarity, strong business ties, and a bucket list that ranges from the streets of London to the Scottish Highlands. But UK entry rules for US citizens changed significantly in 2025, and 2026 has brought further updates that catch many travelers off guard."},{"type":"paragraph","text":"The single most important thing to know: US citizens no longer enter the UK visa-free without any prior formality. Since April 2, 2025, all Americans traveling to the UK for short stays must hold an approved Electronic Travel Authorisation (ETA) before boarding any transport to Britain. Without it, you can be denied boarding before you even leave the United States."},{"type":"section","heading":"Do US Citizens Need a Visa for the UK?","text":"For short stays of up to 6 months (tourism, family visits, business meetings, conferences, short-term study), US citizens do not need a traditional visa. However, since April 2025, they do need a UK Electronic Travel Authorisation (ETA) — a mandatory pre-travel digital permission linked to your passport."},{"type":"section","heading":"The UK ETA: Key Facts (2026)","items":[{"text":"Cost: £16 per person (increased from £10 on February 25, 2026)"},{"text":"Valid for: 2 years or until your passport expires — whichever comes first"},{"text":"Entries: Multiple — unlimited trips during validity"},{"text":"Each visit: Up to 6 months per entry"},{"text":"Processing: Usually minutes; allow up to 3 business days"},{"text":"Application: Online via the official UK government ETA app or the GOV.UK website"}]},{"type":"section","heading":"Long-Stay and Residency Options for Americans","items":[{"text":"Skilled Worker visa — minimum salary £41,700 per year as of 2026"},{"text":"UK Student Visa — requires unconditional university offer and proof of financial means"},{"text":"Family Visa — for joining a UK citizen or settled person"},{"text":"Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR) — permanent residence after 5 continuous years"}]}]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['UK visa', 'US citizens', 'UK ETA', 'UK immigration', '2026'],
  ARRAY['uk-eta-for-us-citizens', 'uk-standard-visitor-visa-us-citizens', 'uk-work-visa-for-americans', 'moving-to-uk-from-usa']
