(
  'uk-eta-for-us-citizens',
  'UK ETA for Americans: What It Is, How to Apply & What Changed in 2026',
  'US citizens now need a UK ETA before every trip to Britain. Here''s exactly what it is, how to apply in minutes, the new £16 fee, and the critical 2026 rule changes you need to know.',
  'uk eta for us citizens',
  'Matthew Lin',
  9,
  '2026-03-04T00:00:00Z',
  'US citizens now need a UK ETA before every trip to Britain. Here''s exactly what it is, how to apply in minutes, the new £16 fee, and the critical 2026 rule changes you need to know.',
  '[{"type":"paragraph","text":"If you haven''t been to the UK since before April 2025, there''s a new step in your pre-trip checklist that didn''t used to exist. Americans now need a UK Electronic Travel Authorisation (ETA) before boarding any transport to Britain — flight, ferry, or Eurostar train."},{"type":"paragraph","text":"It''s not a visa. It doesn''t change what you can do as a visitor. It won''t stamp your passport or appear in any document you carry. But it is now a hard legal requirement, and airlines and transport operators are checking for it."},{"type":"section","heading":"What Changed in 2026","items":[{"text":"Fee increased from £10 to £16 per person effective February 25, 2026","bold":["£16"]},{"text":"Dual British-American citizens must now travel on their British passport — they cannot use a US passport and obtain an ETA","bold":["must travel on their British passport"]}]},{"type":"section","heading":"How to Apply: Step by Step","items":[{"text":"Use the official UK ETA app (iOS/Android) or GOV.UK website — avoid third-party services"},{"text":"Scan your US passport using your phone camera"},{"text":"Take a live selfie for identity verification"},{"text":"Answer questions about your travel plans and background"},{"text":"Pay £16 by card, Apple Pay, or Google Pay"},{"text":"Wait for decision — usually minutes, up to 3 business days"},{"text":"Travel with the same passport you applied with — no printed document needed"}]},{"type":"section","heading":"What the ETA Permits","items":[{"text":"Tourism, leisure, holidays"},{"text":"Visiting family and friends"},{"text":"Business meetings, conferences, negotiations"},{"text":"Short-term study up to 6 months"},{"text":"Transit through UK airports"}]}]'::jsonb,
