  'moving to uk from usa',
  'Matthew Lin',
  11,
  '2026-03-04T00:00:00Z',
  'Thinking of moving to the UK from America? Here''s the complete 2026 guide — every visa route, real costs, NHS access, the path to Indefinite Leave to Remain, and what life actually looks like on the other side.',
  '[{"type":"paragraph","text":"For many Americans, moving to the United Kingdom is a life goal that sits somewhere between deeply romantic and genuinely practical. The appeal is real — a world-class city in London, an extraordinary quality of life in places like Edinburgh or Bristol, strong employment opportunities in finance, tech, and healthcare, and a cultural familiarity that makes the transition less jarring than many other international moves."},{"type":"section","heading":"Choosing Your Route","items":[{"text":"Moving for work: Skilled Worker visa requires a job offer and minimum salary of £41,700","bold":["£41,700"]},{"text":"Moving for family: UK Family Visa requires UK partner earning at least £29,000 per year","bold":["£29,000 per year"]},{"text":"Moving to study: UK Student Visa requires unconditional offer from a licensed institution"},{"text":"Ages 18-30: Youth Mobility Scheme offers 2-year working visa with no salary threshold"}]},{"type":"section","heading":"Real Costs of Moving","items":[{"text":"Skilled Worker visa (3 years): £769 fee + £3,105 IHS = approx. £3,874 upfront"},{"text":"Family visa (2.5 years): £1,258 fee + approx. £2,587 IHS = approx. £3,845 upfront"},{"text":"ILR after 5 years: £3,029 application fee"},{"text":"British citizenship after ILR: £1,605 naturalisation fee"}]},{"type":"section","heading":"The Path to Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR)","items":[{"text":"5 years of continuous lawful residence on a qualifying visa"},{"text":"No more than 180 days outside the UK in any 12-month period"},{"text":"Pass the Life in the UK test"},{"text":"Application fee: £3,029"},{"text":"After ILR: apply for British citizenship after 12 months — dual US-British citizenship is permitted"}]}]'::jsonb,
